Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30}. Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Five mins before the end of cooking, sprinkle the cheese evenly over the potatoes, roast for the remaining time.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150}. Put the @green beans{150} on another baking tray and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat and leave to the side.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the @lamb strips{200} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until nicely browned on the outside, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once browned, remove the meat to a #bowl{}. Put your pan back on the heat and turn the heat to medium-high. Add the onion and mushrooms along with a drizzle of @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir-fry until golden and soft, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the mushrooms are frying, pop your green beans in the oven to roast until crispy but tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

When the mushrooms are browned, stir in the @plain flour{8} and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the lamb strips back in, along with any juices, then pour in the @water for the sauce{200}(ml) and add the @red wine stock paste{28}. Dissolve it with a #spoon{} and bring the mixture to a simmer. Simmer until the sauce is nice and glossy and slightly reduced, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The lamb is safe to eat when the outside is cooked.

Serve whichever way you want... either with the chips alongside the lamb, gravy and mushroom and a good portion of beans, or the steak and gravy served on top of the chips! Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've opted to get lamb strips instead of beef strips, cook the lamb in the same way the recipe tells you to cook the beef.